In order to run the cases other than the single-core case, you must first
generate the particle_input.dat file for each case.

To do this, first build the stand-alone executable of dup.f90, e.g. if using
the GNU compiler simply type 

gfortran dup.f90

Then, starting in BENCH3, for each Size*** case where *** != 001, do

cp Size001/particle_inputs.dat Size004
cd Size004
../a.out 2
cd ..

cp Size001/particle_inputs.dat Size016
cd Size016
../a.out 4
cd ..

cp Size001/particle_inputs.dat Size064
cd Size064
../a.out 8
cd ..

cp Size001/particle_inputs.dat Size256
cd Size256
../a.out 16
cd ..

cp Size001/particle_inputs.dat Size1024
cd Size1024
../a.out 32
cd ..


